*Real-time AM/FM signal generation, reception and analysis using Python, GNU Radio, and ADALM-PLUTO (AD9361)*

---

## ğŸ“ Overview

This repository contains a collection of signal processing experiments and simulations using **Software Defined Radio (SDR)**, specifically the **ADALM-PLUTO (AD9361)** device.  
The aim is to explore **real-time transmission, reception, modulation, and spectral analysis** of RF signals in Python and GNU Radio environments.

---

## ğŸ’» Features

- ğŸ”Š **1 kHz â€“ 6 kHz audio signal generation**
- ğŸŒ€ **Sweep modulation and chirp synthesis**
- ğŸ“¡ **AM signal transmission using SDR TX (centered at 435 MHz)**
- ğŸ§ **Real-time signal reception using SDR RX**
- ğŸ“ˆ **FFT spectrum analysis**
- ğŸŒˆ **Spectrogram (time-frequency) visualization**
- ğŸ Fully implemented in **Python (pyadi-iio, NumPy, matplotlib, SciPy)**  
- ğŸ§± Replicated in **GNU Radio Companion** for live DSP and GUI

